{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"29b2298f-2375-4a2a-9913-cb4c31934076","content":"Found **1 untestable static call** in your project:\n\n**`my_app/views.py:3`** — `datetime.now()`\n\nThis is hard to mock in tests because it's called directly. Recommended fix: use Django's `timezone.now()` (which is easier to mock with `freezegun` or `unittest.mock.patch`) or inject the clock as a dependency:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nYou can then freeze time in tests with `@freeze_gun(\"2026-01-01\")` or `@mock.patch('django.utils.timezone.now')`.\n\nThat's the only instance in this project — small codebase, quick fix!","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9aadc7b7-bcaf-48d8-b852-8acedf637948","outputTokens":194,"requestId":"BC22:1971A6:6F1622:805BDF:69FAA91B"},"id":"b8ced2e8-4540-4987-9b97-9cf8fcbd57cb","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:36:17.707Z","parentId":"03999410-b701-42fb-abab-836045d0d0c2"}
